<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1728,2042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
This is an intermediate-sized, pale-colored species, usually with a very bright yellow color pattern, especially when young (
<figureCitation box="[237,307,1764,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,730,754]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,706]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[151,1436,181,706]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photos of male Megalestes riccii showing color changes with maturing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407487/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The most conspicuous character of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[727,824,1764,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[727,824,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the yellow-colored cerci. This species is distributed in Guangxi, Hunan, Jiangxi, 
<collectingCountry box="[473,558,1800,1826]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and Zhejiang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="265" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1728,2042]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,150,465]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="265" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
There were three named species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[590,716,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,716,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Megalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that have yellow-colored cerci, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[1073,1168,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[1073,1168,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[1181,1274,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[1181,1274,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[1334,1429,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[1334,1429,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[319,390,1872,1898]" name="China" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[401,591,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[401,591,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Megalestes maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[766,852,1872,1898]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. We examined a series of type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in IZAS and IEAS, as well as photos of the 
<typeStatus box="[804,902,1908,1934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[941,1038,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[941,1038,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, kindly provided by Dr. Guanhong Huang from the Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department of 
<collectingCountry box="[974,1111,1944,1970]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
. After studying our series of specimens, including four specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[612,707,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[612,707,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
kindly provided by Mr. Wen-chi Yeh and Dr. Liang-jong Wang from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,298,2016,2042]" name="Taiwan" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, we found no distinct differences among these three. Molecular analysis also implied that they were the same species (
<figureCitation box="[353,421,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Chao, H. - F." box="[442,582,150,177]" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
compared a single male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[891,984,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[891,984,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1134,151,177]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
with type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the results indicated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[539,632,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[539,632,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[850,946,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[850,946,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the longer wings and the obtuse tip of the basal tooth on the paraproct. However, among our series of specimens, the body sizes of some Zhejiang individuals (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[199,296,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[199,296,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were larger than those from 
<collectingCountry box="[633,715,259,285]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[732,826,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[732,826,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the shape of the paraproct basal tooth tip varied randomly. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T." box="[270,531,295,321]" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" pagination="237 - 279" refId="ref15245" refString="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Reels, G. T. (2003) Odonata of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, China, Part 1: Zygoptera. Odonatologica, 32, 237 - 279." type="journal article" year="2003">Wilson &amp; Reels (2003)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[712,809,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[712,809,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has “sharply pointed, bifurcated” tips of the basal tooth on the paraproct. Again, as discussed above, there is also intraspecies variation since our specimens show that both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[151,248,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[151,248,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[305,402,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[305,402,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have the tips obvious or not, and “bifurcated” or not. One individual from Jinxiu (very near the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[422,517,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[422,517,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) even has a very long and pointed tip (
<figureCitation box="[950,1033,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1443,1467]" captionTargetBox="[175,1424,244,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-56@15.[151,1437,237,1419]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Caudal appendages of males (lateral view). a) australis; b) irma, paratype; c) distans, from Yaan, Sichuan; d) distans from Qingchengshan, Chengdu, Sichuan; e) heros; f) omeiensis, paratype; g) kurahashii; h) major; i) haui; j) “palaceus”; k) micans; l) “Chengi,” paratype; m) riccii; n) maai; o) tuska, from Damingshan, Guangxi; p) tuska, from Jinxiu, Guangxi. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407493/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">Fig. 4p</figureCitation>
). Thus, we believe that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1947" box="[1296,1389,403,428]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maai">
<emphasis box="[1296,1389,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. maai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson &amp; Reels" authorityYear="2003" box="[151,248,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuska">
<emphasis box="[151,248,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. tuska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1934" box="[577,674,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="265" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[577,674,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="265">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
